<subsection xml:id="Angle-properties-of-polygons">
    <title>Angle properties of polygons.</title>
        <p>
            <term>What do you understand by the term 'polygon'?</term>
        </p>
        <p>
            A polygon is a two dimensional shape with three or more sides, where the sides are all straight lines.
        </p>
        <p>
            <term>'Poly'</term> is a greek word for <term>'many'</term> and <term>'gon'</term> means <term>'angles'</term>.
        </p>
        <p>
            Examples of polygons include: triangle, quadrilateral, pentagon, hexagon, heptagon, octagon e.t.c. 
        </p>

